node.text:
“To capture these moments with your camera, you have to sacrifice hours of sleep and try to find the best light in the mornings, which in my opinion is the most important thing in a shot. That mysterious and cozy touch can only be achieved at that early time of day. Dolomites is a place that invites you to discover it and want to photograph it with your Sony Alpha from dawn until dusk.” - @onlythenico ⛰️✨ So stunning. 

Shot with Sony Alpha 7 III (currently on sale!) + 24-70mm F2.8 G Master II (1 + 2) + 70-200mm F2.8 G Master OSS II. #SonyAlpha Valid in the US only now thru 1/26.
@soriag5 gracias Edu!! 🙌🏻 espero que ya estés preparado para el próximo viaje!
@phil_sauvage but how much edit is done on those pics?
@piotr_sienkiewicz In my opinion Not so much. I was at Lago di braies several years ago and the lake with the Surroundings are very close to this 👏
@phil_sauvage I see but, I'm quite sure there is much work with colors. Or if it's that in real I'm booking tickets 😁
Awesome shots 😍 this is the reason why i love Sony 😍😍😍
@julientambos one of the best destinations in the world requires that kind of efford ✨

Un rêve de vivre une aventure comme celle-ci... 😭
Je sacrifierai bien plus que des heures de sommeil pour être ici. Merci pour ces magnifiques images 🔥
Awesome shots 😍 this is the reason why i love Sony 😍
@avecnicole 3rd one looks like one of yours!!!
These 3 pictures are so amazing that it's hard to choose which one is the best
@guillenbri the best connection ever created between a photographer and a model who takes risks in photos.
All three photographs are pure art. @onlythenico is, without a doubt, my favorite Spanish photographer!
